headline: Raymond James Welcomes San Diego Advisor Group Managing $1.1 Billion in Assets
summary: St. Petersburg, Fla., Oct. 09, 2025 (GLOBE NEWSWIRE) -- Raymond James (NYSE: RJF) recently welcomed five financial advisors with The Manning Companies (TMC) in San Diego to Raymond James Financial Services (RJFS) – the firm’s independent advisor channel – according to Casey McGee, Western assistant division director for RJFS. The advisors are Michael A. Manning, AIF®, MBA; William B. Corder, AIF®, CPFA®; Roger D. Groves, CLU®; Heather R. Nicholas, AIF®, CLTC®; and Richard Carlquist, CFP®, AIF®.
